@peritus, pretty much all configuration to logging has, by design, global effects. I agree that in this case adding the workaround for others bugs in httplib isn't needed, though, especially since the problem doesn't appear with Python 2.7 or RF 2.7.

If someone has motivation, a bug could be opened to WebTest for registering StreamHandler with sys.stderr that others may have intercepted. They should use sys.__stderr__ instead. StreamHandler uses sys.stderr by default (which IMHO is a bug too) but WebTest actually passes sys.stderr explicitly, at least, here:
https://bitbucket.org/ianb/webtest/src/63d9903c478b/webtest/sel.py

