It really depends on what specifically you are ordering by. Most likely though you don't actually want to sort by a column on all rows on the related model, but just by the maximum or minimum value of that column. In which case you would do something like:

```python
class SomeModel(models.Model):
	date = models.DateTimeField()

# ...

class ThreeManager(models.Manager):

	def get_queryset(self):
		qset = super(ThreeManager, self).get_queryset()
		return qset.annotate(max_date=models.Max('additional__date'))


class Three(models.Model):
    two = models.ForeignKey(Two)
    additional = models.ManyToManyField(SomeModel)

    objects = ThreeManager()

    class Meta:
        ordering = ('-max_date', )
```

