This has to do with a change of the scikit-image `imread` backend of PIMS. Nothing we can do about it, but the following indeed converts a normalized float image to `unit8`. The pipeline trick makes the function evaluate lazily.
```
import pims

@pims.pipeline
def convert_to_uint8(image):
    return (image * 255).astype(np.uint8)

images = convert_to_uint8(frames)
```

